orld, to views of capitalism and science, to blockbuster movies and teenage fashion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aConfucianismxHistoryx21st centuryxChina. 0aConfucianismzChinaxHistoryy21st century. 4aAsian Studies : Confucianism. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aHistory : History. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aHammond, Kenneth J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRichey, Jeffrey L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845493140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438454931423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438454931/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles